 className based registration, or an\\n         * instance-based (for example, self-) registration. Only registrations performed using the five argument\\n         * <code>registerConfigProvider</code> method are persistent.\\n         */\\n        boolean isPersistent();\\n\\n    }\\n\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777531767105}}\n1147:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating reflection requirements**\\n\\nI need to consider reflection metadata for the test nested class and any associated agent records. However, there’s a caution against using reflection directly in tests, unless it’s a natural requirement of the public API. I should set the security property to the class name, and I must ensure there’s a public zero-argument constructor for implementation. Additionally, I'll have to implement the abstract methods from AuthConfigFactory and check how many source lines are left.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_016b2fa145af3bdb0169f2fb7130688193a4b85686f65c5516\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp8vt2QSrYzZDUYQ3GrvLDkAnfp6SNMEWAYi8fP058A-MgLb--98Z_wkn0Seythj1zYL0QjKyM8P0nDVgtzlBMqAqde2tLdm-CdJEfg2albD37Mf97jr3zCvaU8JqRtISbiBR4yY6idC4giY8PbuZ281RsVX07bpLvcbEm69PkHqK6GHeKaO8jI-LXkx8bi0NwnxVJ088UJ7kwNnBFFRFYQIPCnhRJ0sKVTQYCkqCDnI1H3Yzei4ps1QAz9yxEc0c-ugVsZAjLx6s9pfjmNgi16lJ2zVAGMfqQUwZz4IMnyq8io2x9XM1h0gwzNsReBsZDW87wAVwrsVeURcl7QoKEb0b1KR2umNRvYxTS4qB1erTc6ikI-C37S_xqNXsZkv5bcFb_dulBPdYfKIDdfIAMmsOteWPl53UGFS5SV2wYxWWzevB_BWu8HTCOug7dDbNDB5rXZbKkH-5F1cbusN4YI3afjU81oqPFVkOhtsz4guThKo3mMF691f2S83gCzX7XlYjuULdYl3lUqrdOQqG9Gacfj1nWyrU8F1P8BQr9artJXbMaLmuUQ_Or9YfoUbJsTBFTGMCEzOakhkQYRIjEr6F7YoIJhBuEZ2MYfHpGlZ0nkGlo8J3xAtH_AWay41aBZ6OwalaNUvjafPBPxI0Q9ciX7G0zoeo2MJ57zhE_SRrAEJ94HprB88_6JGXP_hT3zuT8BfgCG0k15dH-NjRy-c50q6_HWlAjz3lBWr3IoHer6ykwiFSGuFCeLdlnvq_PdQd9V4ldS4ksXxYJjokw-GkYJk5a8ONpeplBfVo3YLOiKiDrenaf55