\\\"**Evaluating AuthConfigFactory behavior**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering that if the `AuthConfigFactory.factory` stays null after the test, future calls to `getFactory` will fail. It might be better to leave the factory set to the created `TestAuthConfigFactory` along with the class name property. That way, the future `getFactory` can return the factory without using reflection. However, if cleanup cannot restore, we shouldn't unset it. I think it’s wise to set the factory to null before the test to avoid any side effects.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering code placeholders**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about whether I should leave a placeholder for the public or just delete it to reduce noise. Deleting the existing placeholder might be fine, especially since the commit is focused on tests. If all non-active tests are gone, I’ll need to check if there’s any source context, like module-info exports. I might also need to consider package accessibility and naming conventions too. This could really influence my decision!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_3ra3b2XXx6yJqic2yKkdZsXZ|fc_016b2fa145af3bdb0169f2fb88e730819381e98410916cbc00\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find /home/mihailo/git/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/jakarta.authentication/jakarta.authentication-api/3.0.0/main/extracted -type f -maxdepth 10 | sort | sed -n '1,80p'\", \"timeout\": 10}, \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"command\\\":\\\"find /home/mihailo/git/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/jakarta.authentication/jakarta.authentication-api/3.0.0/main/extracted -type f -maxdepth 10 | sort | sed -n '1,80p'\\\",\\\"timeout\\\":10}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 4215, \"output\": 1038, \"cacheRead\": 12288, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 17541, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0