actory(factory);\\\\n+ 48             }\\\\n+ 49         }\\\\n  40     }\\\\n  41 \\\\n  42     @Override\\\\n  43     public AuthConfigProvider getConfigProvider(String layer, String appContext, RegistrationListener listener) {\\\\n     ...\\\", \\\"firstChangedLine\\\": 19}, \\\"isError\\\": false, \\\"timestamp\\\": 1777531858481}}\\n1780:[recv] {\\\"type\\\": \\\"turn_end\\\", \\\"message\\\": {\\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"thinking\\\", \\\"thinking\\\": \\\"**Analyzing context restoration**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering the context restoration for tests. If the context is old and null, it could lead to failures. I think it’s better to leave property and factory null if they’re bad. In the final step, if the previous property is null, I should leave the factory loaded and test the property. But if the previous property is non-null, I’ll restore it and set the factory to null. This should work well, right?\\\", \\\"thinkingSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"rs_016b2fa145af3bdb0169f2fbc2a66c81939402a9d57bd6d833\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"reasoning\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"encrypted_content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gAAAAABp8vvOJNGKTV0xZjm1krdG0Lnt3ArihNSk7vRTJeFsNhTbuno299bITwh2o6J-vj-UxvXrsCRLPeu4Euyq4IBNiBE3Z04HMlKJ9jYZwIsgT7o71cmFtMlbq3kIk_BckZdSCM8uoKDh2dtUM1RSHUs0GSGnnyi-3X76jbYOeeh1WlmPFLLIC_XvIU_hdJGVbg9OL460y4NRc9Vtvifv3sGMIWmEgODZPuYPuWIDl2fPP9zOfMtoFkt2_w3N97UbAGrpFaPIJgeiJc0xrR1ItZcqal6zZ5EW2tDUT0dxEs37vyjpOflXzJ_9DvG8EsifgDmrpziXUMfm41-ER2UA0uM4MCZj8h1S3TswqWrZrYw_dJkTf_FVCuyY5x2yjqWEj9rcSBqT9mtIs-CDhzYsX3tk5Kk_w1x02ikVa4SjDo2lPdSB8yR_2Ov1zmxpDaP7x_fcYs2Y5lFPsU9NjIZc0Mt0tH06i5l-Xa44SdT8r_X8XOD5wMbXkKvGn6szkJABo3C0pkoFs_R68tiEvZQ_LtvWVT7ZpwN8dEDp7N5hLjW6Wlz1pKJ6vxgFfHJTjM3mt2Bqtek0FXwLpmLmqcr3MQ9XBZKxdIWQcLtY8ENHoJpdI7oK_ECfF929drLT4vCvDKv2va1L2DFOpjwcrC5-k2L1s5APL5vDmryHHkBamfLctH5rh24jpcjx1AdG3WWiW2aupXj8F3sSN2yG6et2BDvv9-qMaTEgoEA1JFk6S5wJclmx1tVtIo9Sq418NvuOd5LASp2pEeWoGyp6A2kyu8LqEGLFlGvnb0RyWWWVO4KwiXhvBUaIs